sentences: Originally hailing from the Republic of Panama, Carillo specializes in dance music with a Latin influence.
Rod Carrillo discovered his passion for music when working as a DJ at just 15 years of age.
He regularly worked the nightclub circuit and played various sets on local radio stations.
In 2019, he worked with Ralphi Rosario and Abel Aguilera executive producing and spearheading the duo's first studio album under their alias Rosabel.
The Album was released in April 2019 to positive reviews.
Upon its release, The Album ranked in the top 10 Billboard Dance/Electronic Sales in United States.
In May 2019, artist Eric Redd released his single "Push", which was produced by Carrillo.
Carrillo released his second studio album, Los Sonidos, in 2019.
